Creating a SQL Database

I.	Log into the Windows Azure Management Portal.
II.	In the Home Page choose Create a Resource.						 	
III.	Click Databases and then SQL Database.						 
IV.	Select Subscription and Resource group from the dropdown list.			 
V.	Enter Database name and the name should be unique.	
VI.	For server click create new.
VII.				 
VIII.	Enter server name must be unique, server admin login details  and create valid password and select location and press ok.						
IX.	Click on configure database select compute tier serverless and down data max size to 1GB and press apply.								 	
X.	Press Review+create.									 
XI.	Click on create.										 
XII.	Go to your created resource and press set server firewall. 				 
XIII.	Click on Add client IP.								 
XIV.	Click save.  				
     





